taints are set on nodes, tolerance is set on pods

k taint nodes node-name key=value:taint-effect
there are 3 types of taint-effect: NoSchedule, PreferNoSchedule, NoExecute(if a taint has been applied to a node, the existing pods will be killed)
eg. k taint nodes node1 app=myapp:NoSchedule

tolerations are defined in metadata.spec.tolerations in pod-definition.yaml file

taints and tolerations setting is only working for nodes selecting which pods are allowed to go on that node, but the pod which has a certain tolerance doesnt always
go the that node that has the same taint, it can go to another node which doesnt have any taint apllied.
t omake sure that pod goes to a certain node, we need to apply affinity.

it's all happening on work nodes, for master node, it auto-apply taint already:
$ k describe node kubemaster | grep Taint
Taint:     node-role.kubenetes.io/master: NoSchedule
